1.00	Khaleda	Khaleda Zia	Begum Khaleda Zia (Bengali: ) is the former First Lady of Bangladesh (1977–1981), and then Prime Minister of Bangladesh, having served from 1991 to 1996, becoming the first woman in the country's history and second in the Muslim world (only after Ms Benazir Bhutto of Pakistan in 1988–1990) to head a democratic government as prime minister. She served again from 2001 until 2006. She is the widow of the President and former army chief Ziaur Rahman, who was assassinated in 1981, and leads his old party, the Bangladesh Nationalist Party.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Begum_Zia_Book-opening_Ceremony%2C_1_Mar%2C_2010.jpg/220px-Begum_Zia_Book-opening_Ceremony%2C_1_Mar%2C_2010.jpg
